{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb537c944-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s593"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"593"},"text":"§ 593.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Hiring authority","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In hiring personnel for the Office, the Secretary shall have the hiring and management authorities provided in section 1101 ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002097"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002097"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of the Strom Thurmond National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1999 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3104"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 3104","children":[],"tail":" note). The term of appointments for employees under subsection (c)(1) of such section may not exceed 5 years before granting any extension under subsection (c)(2) of such section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb537c945-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296/tXIX/s1924"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296, title XIX, § 1924","children":[],"tail":", formerly title XVIII, § 1803, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/347/tV/s501/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–347, title V, § 501(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1934"},"text":"120 Stat. 1934","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered title XIX, § 1903, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/53/tI/s104/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–53, title I, § 104(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 20